 Scleroderma or Systemic Sclerosis (SC) is a chronic autoimmune disease of the connective tissue with an incidence of 1: 10000- 1: 30000.

 In Greece it is estimated that there are approximately 2,500 patients.

 The disease usually affects women aged 40-60 years, and the incidence is four women to one man.

 The pathogenesis of the disease is unknown, while the main causes are considered genetic and environmental factors.

 Two of the most critical complications of the disease, are the Pulmonary Arterial Hypertension, which occurs in patients with SC approximately 8-12% of patients, being the main cause of death, and digital ulcers that occur in 30-60 % of patients and are painful sores on the fingers.

