 The digital ulcers adversely affect the quality of life of patients, even the simple daily activities and can lead to serious complications, such as amputation.

 The symptoms of scleroderma can vary between patients and may not be typical of this disease, at least in the early stages, making it difficult to diagnose.

 Two of the early symptoms are disturbance of blood supply to the extremities by a color change of the skin of the fingers, alternately pallor-cyanation-redness (Raynaud phenomenon) and rigid edematous fingers.

